  "prompt": "How do you post blogs on Quora?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Quora discontinued its blogging platform known as \"Quora Blogs\" in 2018. Before then, users could write longer-form content similar to blog posts directly on Quora. However, currently, Quora's primary focus is on the Q&A format. \n\nIf you want to share detailed content on Quora, here are some alternatives:\n\n1. **Answer Questions:** You can write comprehensive answers to questions on topics you're knowledgeable about. If there's no existing question that fits, you can phrase a new question and then answer it yourself right afterward.\n\n2. **Create a Space:** Quora Spaces allow users to curate content around specific themes. You can use a Space to share your content and gather related discussions and posts.\n\n3. **Use Quora's Partner Program:** If you're part of Quora\u2019s Partner Program, you might have a bit more flexibility in terms of how you can create and share content.\n\n4. **Link to External Blogs:** While you can't directly post blog content, you can reference and link to your external blog posts in your answers, providing valuable insights and driving traffic to your blog.\n\nWhen using Quora for content, always ensure your posts adhere to Quora\u2019s policies and community guidelines. Avoid overly promotional content, and focus on adding value to the conversation.",
